additionalNames.name: Koog aan de Zaan
additionalNames.long: Koog aan de Zaan, The Netherlands

reviews.title: Quick pancake? This is the right address!
reviews.text: For a quick bite, pancakes are always a good idea. The Honeypot in Epe is then a very good choice! We enjoyed pancakes with cheese and with ginger, which were all well cooked and sufficient in size. With the cheese pancake I was given the choice whether to bake the cheese or not. Nice that they leave that choice to the guest. The coffee was delicious and the service very fast and friendly. Only downside was that it was quite noisy, so we could not always understand each other well.

reviews.title: Fine and cozy and tasty pancakes
reviews.text:
We hadn't been to this pancake house in years. Today we ate here again and we were not disappointed. After a very friendly reception we decided to have a menu, which consisted of a soup, a pancake and a dessert. We were allowed to choose the soup and kind of pancake with two ingredients. 
Everything has tasted very good at a very attractive price, certainly not insignificant in these expensive hospitality times. Overall we were happy and the homely atmosphere in this restaurant certainly contributed to that. When we get back around, we'll come back.

reviews.title: Delicious food! TOP.
reviews.text:
Really a pancake house in terms of entourage, 
Delicious food!! Smooth friendly service! A little less questions would you like? Do you still want that or that? Could be. 
Can also seem too pushy.
But definitely worth repeating! 
Good Cook kitchen team! Compliments.

reviews.title: Nice, cozy and very friendly staff
reviews.text: We ate the savoury Pastrami and French pancakes. Because it was so good we returned a few days later, this time for a pancake like four o'clock. Very tasty again. Only downside: the jam and honey were standard industrial packaging, for that price it could be fresh.

reviews.title: Fresh delicious pancakes
reviews.text: Cozy little gem with super delicious homemade pancakes, both dessert and food pancakes. They tasted wonderful and are a place where there is also room for children.

reviews.title: Welcoming staff and delicious food.
reviews.text:
We could have a delicious dinner there and take the dog with us. Which is important to us because we don't want to leave him alone in a strange hotel room during our stay in the Veluwe. It was no problem at all and he was given water, sweets and a spot was made available for him at the table.
Furthermore, the food was super fresh and tasty.
The service is very hospitable and friendly.
We will definitely come back.

reviews.title: gets less
reviews.text:
Went to the honey pot regularly
The pancake with ham is very sparsely topped, in contrast to the past.
Apparently the cost of ingredients is being approached in this wrong way.
€1 for a glass of tap water is also daring and not exactly customer-friendly.
Operation is correct despite its youth. Pancake tastes good too.

reviews.title: Cozy atmosphere and tasty pancakes
reviews.text:
Ate pancakes on Sunday August 13. Pancakes were fine. Well baked and richly topped.
The girls at the service were friendly and very fast.
I was amazed at how hard these young girls were working.
A little tip: When people come in and are just sitting down, give them 2 minutes.
We had just taken our seat and someone immediately came to our table to ask what we wanted to drink.
However well-intentioned, sometimes it is a bit too fast and you want to check which beers/drinks are on the menu.
Or else give people some time and come back a few minutes later to take the order.

reviews.title: Gezellig
reviews.text: Very cosy place, located nearby a parking place, very easy to find. The food is good, the pancakes are enormous, the service is fast and the staff friendly. We asked to change one ingredient in the menu and it was not a problem. Very pleasant for a relax family evening.

reviews.title: Family dinner
reviews.text: When we arrived in Holland my daughters wanted to go to a pannenkoeken huis. Their grandparents took us to the Honingpot. They had a lot to choose from even strange combinations.  But they were delicious.

reviews.title: Good meal
reviews.text: We had an excellent meal and a massive plate full! A very broad choice of different pancakes, sweet and savory. The service was very good and friendly. Very child orientated, but not so it bothered other diners. The kids have their own playroom.

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

tripContent.title: Experience vibrant art and culture in Fort Myers
tripContent.description: There’s so much more to soak up than the sun in and around Fort Myers. This itinerary is designed for art-lovers, who can take in the visual and performing arts scene, learn about the area’s fascinating history, and go for a scenic stroll to enjoy neighborhood murals and outdoor art installations.

articleContent.title: 5 perfect days in New York City

seoInfo.metaDescription: More than 60 million people visit New York City every year, and a huge percentage of them only hit the big sites—Times Square, the Empire State Building, etc. I get it: They’re iconic. But as someone who has lived in this city for more than 30 years, I’m here to tell you that you’re missing out if you don’t mix in some off-the-beaten path locations. Luckily, five days gives you plenty of time to do just that.
